track_notes:
From Puget-Theniers it is a nice walk to the crest, 
 you can use the via-ferrata, if you want fun! The trig point is in the forest and a vertical is bestter than a dipole.
Walk in the forest, until the trig point in the forest where it is difficult to setup a dipole!

This is not a must. You can park anywhere at the village or very near the starting path. The track is good until the crest then you must find your way in between trees to reach the trig point 1070m.
During the walk there are parts where you must behave carefully. On summit you cannot use a large antenna system, because of the trees. Use a vertical antenna recommended. In autum there may be hunters, you must then wear colored clothes.
